member.summary:
Tracer class helps to implement performance tracing. It is mostly used to log method 
entry/exit and duration. Lifetime of the Tracer object will determine the beginning and 
the end of the trace. The trace message will include, method being traced, start time, 
end time and duration.

To instrument a method for the performance tracing  wrap the whole method body into the 
using statement like this

void Foo()
{
    using (new Tracer(TraceLayer.Provider))
    {
        // Method implementation goes here.
    }
}

This class uses TraceManager to log the trace messages.
